                            <path d="M62.4861 46.9572L62.4861 46.9573L62.4904 46.9601C62.7426 47.1282 62.9635 47.5124 63.0268 47.9551C63.0173 48.3098 62.8402 48.6379 62.4814 48.8957L40.8077 63.6669L40.7984 63.6733L40.7893 63.6801C40.6324 63.7978 40.4094 63.8563 40.1228 63.8563C39.9208 63.8563 39.7474 63.8043 39.6407 63.7331L39.6148 63.7159L39.5869 63.7019C39.2027 63.5098 38.9658 63.1298 38.9658 62.6993V33.1504C38.9658 32.7199 39.2027 32.3399 39.5869 32.1478L39.6082 32.1372L39.6283 32.1246C39.9915 31.8976 40.4626 31.9364 40.7987 32.1765L40.7986 32.1766L40.8077 32.1828L62.4861 46.9572Z" fill="#2A2065" stroke="#2A2065" />
                        </svg>
                    </div>
                    </div>
                    <!-- Progress Bar -->
                    <div class="progress-bar" id="progress-bar">
                        <!-- Slider -->
                        <svg class="slider" id="slider" draggable="true" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="10" height="15" viewBox="0 0 10 15" fill="none">
                            <ellipse cx="4.91647" cy="7.35289" rx="4.58248" ry="7.30504" fill="white" />
                        </svg>
                    </div>
                    <div id="timer" style="color: white; margin-top: 10px; text-align: center;"></div>
                    <!-- Play/Pause Button -->
                    

                </div>
            </div>
    
            <!-- Text Box -->
            <div class="box text-box">
                <div class="box-heading">The Brave Butterfly and the Asteroid Adventure</div>
                <div class="box-subtext">Once upon a time in the enchanting world of the asteroid shower, there lived a brave butterfly named Flutter. Flutter was known for her vibrant wings and her kind heart. One day, as the asteroids streaked across the sky, Flutter noticed a group of lost baby birds chirping for help.\n\nWith a flutter of her delicate wings, Flutter flew towards the distressed birds. She listened to their sad chirps and realized that they had been separated from their mother during the chaos of the asteroid shower. Determined to help, Flutter devised a plan.\n\nFlutter guided the baby birds through the dense forest, using her keen eyes to spot landmarks and navigate the tricky terrain. She flew from tree to tree, ensuring that the little birds followed in her path. As they journeyed together, Flutter sang a cheerful tune to keep their spirits high.\n\nJust when they were nearing the safety of their mother, a strong gust of wind blew through the forest, scattering the birds in different directions. Flutter's heart sank as she watched them disappear into the tangle of trees.\n\nBut Flutter was not one to give up easily. She flew in every direction, searching tirelessly for the lost birds. Her wings fluttered with determination as she called out to them, hoping they would hear her voice amidst the chaos of the asteroid shower.\n\nAfter what seemed like an eternity, Flutter finally found all the lost birds. With a sense of relief and joy, she brought them back together. The little birds chirped happily as they were reunited with their mother.\n\nAs a reward for her bravery and kindness, the birds' mother thanked Flutter and offered her a special gift. She gently brushed her wing against Flutter's, and in an instant, her wings transformed into a dazzling display of colors.\n\nFrom that day forward, Flutter became known as the Butterfly of Kindness. She continued to help those in need, spreading joy and happiness wherever she went.</div>
            </div>
        </div>
